193
00:08:30,344 --> 00:08:32,560
Becky, can you
wiggle your left toes?

194
00:08:34,431 --> 00:08:36,997
Great. How about your right?

195
00:08:38,001 --> 00:08:40,085
I... I...

196
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:42,337
can't move my leg.

197
00:08:42,372 --> 00:08:44,188
What's going on?

198
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:48,487
Ah, pupils are
equal and reactive.

199
00:08:48,511 --> 00:08:50,028
This shouldn't need stitches.

200
00:08:50,063 --> 00:08:51,263
How you feeling?

201
00:08:51,298 --> 00:08:53,731
Ah, just-just a headache.

202
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:55,595
Maybe my eyes
are a little bit blurry.

203
00:08:55,619 --> 00:08:58,419
Okay, possible concussion.
We'll run some tests.

204
00:08:58,455 --> 00:09:01,072
Hey, I got another patient.

205
00:09:01,108 --> 00:09:03,169
- I got to go. You good?
- Good.

206
00:09:03,193 --> 00:09:04,893
- Sure?
- Mm.

207
00:09:04,928 --> 00:09:06,171
- John?
- Mm.

208
00:09:06,195 --> 00:09:07,723
- Squeeze my fingers.
- Ah.

209
00:09:07,747 --> 00:09:09,397
Squeeze my fingers. Good. Good.

210
00:09:09,432 --> 00:09:11,115
So you live here in Atlanta?

211
00:09:11,150 --> 00:09:15,003
Yeah, we do, but we spend
most of our time on the road.

212
00:09:16,756 --> 00:09:19,207
- Oh, yeah, why's that?
- Uh, well,

213
00:09:19,242 --> 00:09:24,212
Becky and I started the Copple
Foundation about 15 years ago.

214
00:09:24,247 --> 00:09:27,115
All right, push on the gas.
Push on the gas. That's good.

215
00:09:27,150 --> 00:09:30,134
Yeah, we, uh, serve the causes

216
00:09:30,169 --> 00:09:32,120
that we're most
passionate about.

217
00:09:32,155 --> 00:09:34,255
Health care is one of them.

218
00:09:34,290 --> 00:09:36,758
And that is why we
know this man so well.

219
00:09:36,793 --> 00:09:39,293
John.

