00:13:25,788 --> 00:13:27,972
the plan is, we
remove the propeller,

311
00:13:28,008 --> 00:13:30,035
stop the bleeding before
she exsanguinates.

312
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:33,610
Then, if we succeed,
reattaching her pelvis

313
00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:36,380
to her spine will not
be a walk in the park.

314
00:13:36,415 --> 00:13:39,300
I'll prep the OR.

315
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:42,982
What's the story?

316
00:13:43,006 --> 00:13:45,039
TBI.

317
00:13:45,075 --> 00:13:48,192
History of a benign brain tumor
that was successfully removed,

318
00:13:48,228 --> 00:13:51,179
but it's regrown.

319
00:13:51,231 --> 00:13:53,159
Well, hopefully
it's still benign.

320
00:13:53,183 --> 00:13:55,833
I'll send it to pathology
when I take it out.

321
00:13:55,868 --> 00:13:59,153
I'm gonna need to review his
prior scans and path reports.

322
00:13:59,189 --> 00:14:02,039
- Mm-hmm.
- There's also
an associated hemorrhage.

323
00:14:02,074 --> 00:14:05,243
- Is he symptomatic?
