327
00:14:13,286 --> 00:14:15,753
That's likely related
to dehydration.

328
00:14:15,788 --> 00:14:18,172
Otherwise, labs
were unremarkable.

329
00:14:18,208 --> 00:14:21,075
All right. I'll take
him to my OR.

330
00:14:25,882 --> 00:14:27,802
Sir, you need to
stay in your bed.

331
00:14:28,717 --> 00:14:30,268
And keep your pants on.

332
00:14:30,303 --> 00:14:31,869
L-Look.

333
00:14:34,073 --> 00:14:36,073
Fasciculations?

334
00:14:37,310 --> 00:14:39,839
- When did it start?
- A few minutes ago.

335
00:14:39,863 --> 00:14:42,880
- Let's get another
full set of labs.
- Right.

336
00:14:42,915 --> 00:14:45,511
We'll check for any
electrolyte abnormalities.

337
00:14:45,535 --> 00:14:48,002
Should I, uh, cancel
Waffle Wednesday?

338
00:14:48,038 --> 00:14:50,121
Maybe just reschedule
till next week.

339
00:14:50,156 --> 00:14:51,466
- A - little help over here!

340
00:14:51,490 --> 00:14:54,041
Respiratory distress, Bay Eight.

341
00:14:54,094 --> 00:14:55,934
- Pravesh.
- Stay there.

342
00:14:56,212 --> 00:14:58,045
Get me an intubation kit.

343
00:14:58,080 --> 00:15:02,083
She started to wheeze and
couldn't clear her secretions.

344
00:15:02,118 --> 00:15:03,896
We tried BiPap and
she became altered

345
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:05,898
and we couldn't get
her sats over 72%.

346
00:15:19,435 --> 00:15:21,803
Mild crackles bilaterally.
Increase the PEEP.

347
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:25,990
PEEP is up to 15.

348
00:15:26,025 --> 00:15:27,608
Okay, that bought us some room.

349
00:15:27,643 --> 00:15:28,988
But she's still
skimming the treetops.

350
00:15:29,012 --> 00:15:31,173
All right, let's get a blood
gas and a chest X-ray.

351
00:15:31,197 --> 00:15:34,165
And write her for broad-spectrum
antibiotics with cultures first.

352
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:36,800
Once we get the gas, we'll
put her on ARDSNet protocol.

353
00:15:36,836 --> 00:15:38,953
If her oxygenation
is still tenuous,

354
00:15:38,988 --> 00:15:40,738
we'll start inhaled epo.

355
00:15:40,774 --> 00:15:42,467
Good plan. But this is strange.

356
00:15:42,491 --> 00:15:43,969
I mean, she came in with
a headache, for God's sake.

357
00:15:43,993 --> 00:15:45,988
And now she's very
close to max vent settings.

358
00:15:46,012 --> 00:15:48,979
We need to figure
this out. And fast.

359
00:15:55,989 --> 00:15:57,671
Can I talk to my wife?

360
00:15:57,707 --> 00:15:59,602
We need to get you
both in ORs ASAP.

361
00:15:59,626 --> 00:16:00,808
No, no, please. I just...

362
00:16:00,844 --> 00:16:02,087
- I need a sec.
- We have to be quick, though.

363
00:16:02,111 --> 00:16:04,195
Hold up, hold up.

364
00:16:06,182 --> 00:16:09,200
I know what you're gonna
say. We're in good hands.

365
00:16:09,235 --> 00:16:10,668
We're both gonna be fine.

366
00:16:10,703 --> 00:16:12,152
You love me.

367
00:16:13,005 --> 00:16:15,105
I was gonna lead
with "I love you."

368
00:16:15,141 --> 00:16:18,209
But, yes, all of that.

369
00:16:18,244 --> 00:16:20,193
Then I'll see you tonight.

370
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:23,530
Make sure we're in a
recovery room together.

371
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:31,605
In our 20 years of marriage,

372
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:33,858
we've never spent a night apart.

373
00:16:33,893 --> 00:16:36,305
We wouldn't want to
break a streak like that.

374
00:16:36,329 --> 00:16:37,990
Well, you've got two softies

375
00:16:38,014 --> 00:16:39,491
who'll do our best
to make it happen,

376
00:16:39,515 --> 00:16:41,282
but right now we got to go.

377
00:16:41,317 --> 00:16:42,561
I love you.

378
00:16:42,585 --> 00:16:45,236
- I love you.
- I love you.

379
00:16:58,084 --> 00:16:59,499
Hey.

380
00:16:59,535 --> 00:17:01,096
<i>How you feeling?</i>

381
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:04,555
Better. Thank you.

382
00:17:04,590 --> 00:17:06,557
It's so quiet. Where are you?

383
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:09,727
Our supply closet.

384
00:17:09,762 --> 00:17:11,845
Oh, it's<i> our</i> supply closet now?

385
00:17:11,881 --> 00:17:14,215
Well, we-we share it
with Jess and Irving,

386
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:15,750
but it's mostly ours.

387
00:17:18,804 --> 00:17:20,755
You okay?

388
00:17:21,808 --> 00:17:23,774
Nic,

389
00:17:23,809 --> 00:17:26,760
I just...

390
00:17:26,796 --> 00:17:30,063
I just want to say
thank you for...

391
00:17:31,784 --> 00:17:33,751
for being there

392
00:17:33,786 --> 00:17:37,254
<i>and for, for never doubting
that I would be okay</i>

393
00:17:37,289 --> 00:17:40,491
<i>and for helping me.</i>

394
00:17:42,612 --> 00:17:44,578
Helping me find
my way back here.

395
00:17:44,614 --> 00:17:47,114
You don't need to thank me.

396
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:49,099
Yes.

397
00:17:49,135 --> 00:17:51,135
I do.

398
00:17:53,339 --> 00:17:55,122
<i>Hey.</i>

399
00:17:55,157 --> 00:17:57,124
<i>You'd do the same for me.</i>

400
00:17:59,945 --> 00:18:01,223
But you need to
get back to work.

401
00:18:01,247 --> 00:18:02,808
People are gonna
think you lost your mind,

402
00:18:02,832 --> 00:18:04,794
talking to yourself
alone in a supply closet

403
00:18:04,818 --> 00:18:06,049
on your first day back.

404
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:10,621
That's fair. That's fair.

405
00:18:10,656 --> 00:18:13,090
<i>I'll get home as soon as I ca.</i>

406
00:18:13,126 --> 00:18:15,309
I know you will.

407
00:18:15,345 --> 00:18:17,461
I'll see you tonight.

408
00:18:22,135 --> 00:18:23,617
Again?

409
00:18:23,652 --> 00:18:27,088
Unfortunately, Raj's bathroom
situation has escalated.

410
00:18:27,123 --> 00:18:29,151
But all of his stool studies
have come back negative.

411
00:18:29,175 --> 00:18:30,624
Mr. Corson's pants

412
00:18:30,660 --> 00:18:33,060
are back on, but he's
still having fasciculations,

413
00:18:33,096 --> 00:18:35,016
and he's started
to act confused.

414
00:18:38,868 --> 00:18:41,334
What?

415
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:45,289
Pravesh. What's up?

416
00:18:50,012 --> 00:18:52,029
MUDDLES.

417
00:18:52,065 --> 00:18:54,531
I haven't heard that term
since I was in medical school.

418
00:18:54,567 --> 00:18:56,317
Meiosis, urination...

419
00:18:56,352 --> 00:18:57,968
Diarrhea, diaphoresis...

420
00:18:58,004 --> 00:19:00,370
Lacrimation, excitation of
the central nervous system,

421
00:19:00,406 --> 00:19:02,122
salivation.

422
00:19:02,158 --> 00:19:03,874
Yeah, so, if you add

423
00:19:03,909 --> 00:19:05,320
Doug, Cynthia and
Raj's symptoms together,

424
00:19:05,344 --> 00:19:07,661
it is textbook
organophosphate poisoning.

425
00:19:07,696 --> 00:19:09,725
How do three patients who
have nothing in common

426
00:19:09,749 --> 00:19:11,494
get exposed to a
toxin that's only found

427
00:19:11,518 --> 00:19:13,496
- in pesticides
and chemical weapons?
- I don't know.

428
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:16,720
But they're all showing
different signs of exposure.

429
00:19:18,057 --> 00:19:20,441
If it is, we need
to treat them fast.

430
00:19:20,476 --> 00:19:22,809
Organophosphate poisoning
can progress rapidly.

431
00:19:22,862 --> 00:19:25,179
Hundley, push atropine
and one gram of 2-PAM

432
00:19:25,214 --> 00:19:27,054
- for all three of them.
- On it.

433
00:19:31,353 --> 00:19:33,020
Dr. Okafor,

434
00:19:33,055 --> 00:19:34,232
why don't you give
that propeller blade

435
00:19:34,256 --> 00:19:35,890
a nice, big tug.

436
00:19:37,944 --> 00:19:39,644
It's not budging.

437
00:19:39,679 --> 00:19:41,056
It's stuck in the SI joint.

438
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:43,000
You have to pull
with more force.

439
00:19:45,251 --> 00:19:47,335
Put your back into it, dear.

440
00:19:50,389 --> 00:19:51,688
Okay, it's not working.

441
00:19:51,724 --> 00:19:52,901
Step aside.

442
00:19:52,925 --> 00:19:56,227
I've got Excalibur.

443
00:20:05,721 --> 00:20:07,104
Damn.

444
00:20:07,140 --> 00:20:09,106
- It won't come out.
- Mm-hmm.

445
00:20:09,141 --> 00:20:10,874
Allow me.

446
00:20:11,910 --> 00:20:15,329
Ortho isn't just
about brute strength.

447
00:20:15,365 --> 00:20:17,531
Sometimes you have to
think outside of the box.

448
00:20:17,566 --> 00:20:18,583
Hammer, please?

449
00:20:20,153 --> 00:20:21,936
And<i> then</i> use brute strength.

450
00:20:23,039 --> 00:20:24,455
Get ready.

451
00:20:28,978 --> 00:20:30,288
Suction.

452
00:20:30,312 --> 00:20:32,232
- Retractors.
- Sutures.

453
00:20:35,818 --> 00:20:37,184
What are the odds

454
00:20:37,219 --> 00:20:39,687
a benign brain tumor regrows?

455
00:20:39,722 --> 00:20:42,039
Well, it's rare,
but it can happen.

456
00:20:42,075 --> 00:20:44,392
Don't worry. I'm
here to deal with that.

457
00:20:44,427 --> 00:20:46,037
We're gonna proceed
with the craniotomy

458
00:20:46,061 --> 00:20:47,923
- to remove the tumor.
- Copy that.

459
00:20:47,947 --> 00:20:49,930
I'll get scrubbed up.

460
00:20:52,118 --> 00:20:53,751
Thank you, Dr. Cain.

461
00:20:53,786 --> 00:20:55,426
You're welcome.

462
00:21:02,028 --> 00:21:04,778
John, I'm gonna
administer the propofol now.

463
00:21:04,813 --> 00:21:08,115
Start counting
backwards for me from ten.

464
00:21:17,543 --> 00:21:20,093
Just breathe.

465
00:21:21,831 --> 00:21:23,146
<i>What'd you give him?</i>

466
00:21:23,182 --> 00:21:25,077
Just relax. Just breathe.

467
00:21:25,101 --> 00:21:26,984
<i>What did you give him?</i>

468
00:21:27,019 --> 00:21:28,080
I haven't given
him anything yet.

469
00:21:28,104 --> 00:21:29,364
You must have done something.

470
00:21:29,388 --> 00:21:30,599
He's tach'ing away in the 150s.

471
00:21:30,623 --> 00:21:32,356
His BP shot up to 180s.

472
00:21:32,391 --> 00:21:34,086
- It hurts!
- What?

473
00:21:34,110 --> 00:21:36,138
- Where do you... Where does
it hurt? Tell me what hurts.
- It hurts!

474
00:21:36,162 --> 00:21:38,173
- What's-what's hurt? What hurts?
- My stomach!

475
00:21:38,197 --> 00:21:40,426
Your stomach?

476
00:21:40,450 --> 00:21:41,999
Abort the surgery!

477
00:21:48,374 --> 00:21:50,786
Dr. Austin, you're
on the left pelvis.

478
00:21:50,810 --> 00:21:52,438
Dr. Okafor, you're on the right.

479
00:21:52,462 --> 00:21:56,497
Fasten this obtrusive
instrument on each side.

480
00:21:56,532 --> 00:22:00,017
Now for the most
critical part of the surgery.

481
00:22:00,052 --> 00:22:03,020
We must bring her pelvis
and spine back into alignment.

482
00:22:03,056 --> 00:22:05,567
- We're gonna
reduce her SI joint?
- Correct.

483
00:22:05,591 --> 00:22:09,026
You will both push your side of
the pelvis towards one another.

484
00:22:09,062 --> 00:22:10,878
How hard do we push?

485
00:22:10,913 --> 00:22:12,396
It must be equal pressure.

486
00:22:12,431 --> 00:22:14,042
And what if one pushes
harder than the other?

487
00:22:14,066 --> 00:22:16,883
Then her pelvis will be
misaligned from her spine.

488
00:22:16,919 --> 00:22:19,570
We could crush her sacral
nerves and leave her paralyzed.

489
00:22:19,605 --> 00:22:23,157
You must be perfectly in sync.

490
00:22:23,192 --> 00:22:24,858
I know I can count on you both.

491
00:22:24,911 --> 00:22:26,004
We got this.

492
00:22:26,028 --> 00:22:27,548
On three?

493
00:22:28,847 --> 00:22:32,500
One, two, three.

494
00:22:33,553 --> 00:22:35,033
Slowly.

495
00:22:37,006 --> 00:22:39,540
A little more pressure
from you both.

496
00:22:43,696 --> 00:22:45,028
Feeling some resistance.

497
00:22:45,064 --> 00:22:46,704
I'll adjust.

498
00:22:50,069 --> 00:22:51,902
Stop.

499
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:58,008
How did we do?

500
00:22:58,043 --> 00:23:00,244
That's anatomic.

501
00:23:01,580 --> 00:23:04,064
I've never seen a
more perfect alignment.

502
00:23:04,099 --> 00:23:06,366
Game, set...

503
00:23:06,401 --> 00:23:07,951
Match.

504
00:23:11,590 --> 00:23:15,459
My patient is stagnating in
the ICU after an aborted surgery

505
00:23:15,494 --> 00:23:17,110
because something you missed.

506
00:23:17,145 --> 00:23:19,763
We don't know that yet.

507
00:23:19,798 --> 00:23:22,032
Then what do you know?

508
00:23:22,068 --> 00:23:24,863
- You're the internist
here, right?
- Mm-hmm.

509
00:23:24,887 --> 00:23:27,905
In the great ecosystem
of this hospital, a flea.

510
00:23:29,474 --> 00:23:31,441
You had one job:

511
00:23:31,477 --> 00:23:33,710
to make sure my patient
was tuned up for surgery.

