00:24:58,364 --> 00:25:00,397
but I have been conned before.

549
00:25:00,432 --> 00:25:03,617
So, woman-to-woman,
off the record,

550
00:25:03,652 --> 00:25:06,720
jump in or run like hell?

551
00:25:15,197 --> 00:25:17,525
All three patients
have stabilized.

552
00:25:17,549 --> 00:25:18,965
Cynthia just got extubated.

553
00:25:19,001 --> 00:25:20,695
- So you were right.
- Yeah.

554
00:25:20,719 --> 00:25:24,171
But how do three
people with no connection

555
00:25:24,206 --> 00:25:27,308
end up with the same
rare poison in their system?

556
00:25:27,343 --> 00:25:29,237
First, we find out. Then
we call County Public Health

557
00:25:29,261 --> 00:25:31,044
and stop whatever caused this.

558
00:25:33,532 --> 00:25:35,065
So, you live nearby in...?

559
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:37,034
- Savannah.
- Chamblee.

560
00:25:37,069 --> 00:25:38,836
Sandy Springs.

561
00:25:38,871 --> 00:25:40,115
Any recent exposure
to chemicals?

562
00:25:40,139 --> 00:25:43,089
- No.
- No.

563
00:25:43,125 --> 00:25:45,475
I bought a can of body spray.

564
00:25:46,528 --> 00:25:48,445
Has anyone sprayed insecticides

565
00:25:48,480 --> 00:25:49,746
near your home or your garden?

566
00:25:49,782 --> 00:25:51,164
I don't have a garden.

567
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:52,515
Not that I'm aware of.

568
00:25:52,551 --> 00:25:53,945
No.

569
00:25:53,969 --> 00:25:56,086
Any vitamins or supplements?

570
00:25:57,122 --> 00:25:58,755
Yeah.

571
00:25:58,790 --> 00:26:01,408
Yeah, I just picked
up a new one.

572
00:26:01,443 --> 00:26:02,559
Um...

573
00:26:02,594 --> 00:26:04,395
3, uh... 3B something.

574
00:26:04,430 --> 00:26:05,512
3B Life.

575
00:26:05,547 --> 00:26:07,013
That's it.

576
00:26:07,049 --> 00:26:08,777
Hey, fingers crossed, I look
just as good as that doctor

577
00:26:08,801 --> 00:26:10,241
on the label when
I'm his age, right?

578
00:26:14,140 --> 00:26:15,371
Three different patients...

579
00:26:15,407 --> 00:26:17,035
All with organophosphate
poisoning.

580
00:26:17,059 --> 00:26:18,091
All on 3B Life.

581
00:26:18,127 --> 00:26:20,577
Well, maybe they use
the same cleaning supplies

582
00:26:20,612 --> 00:26:21,612
or pesticides.

583
00:26:21,647 --> 00:26:23,697
We did extensive
patient histories.

584
00:26:23,732 --> 00:26:25,494
You can't possibly
know everything

585
00:26:25,518 --> 00:26:26,778
that they came
in contact with...

586
00:26:26,802 --> 00:26:28,718
Yes, but, right now,

587
00:26:28,754 --> 00:26:30,332
the only link that we do
have is your supplement.

588
00:26:30,356 --> 00:26:32,806
- How widely was it distributed?
- Wide.

589
00:26:32,842 --> 00:26:35,119
Okay. We need to call Public
Health and warn them about it.

590
00:26:35,143 --> 00:26:36,060
That's ridiculously premature.

591
00:26:36,095 --> 00:26:39,079
You can't call the
CDC on three patients.

592
00:26:39,114 --> 00:26:41,326
Dr. Bell, I know that you
have a personal stake in this,

593
00:26:41,350 --> 00:26:43,316
- but we have to...
- Okay.

594
00:26:43,352 --> 00:26:46,720
Maybe, maybe they have
other things in common.

595
00:26:46,755 --> 00:26:49,122
And if we act too quickly,
we'll destroy the reputation

596
00:26:49,175 --> 00:26:51,941
of a good product
that is helping people,

597
00:26:51,977 --> 00:26:52,926
not to mention me.

598
00:26:52,961 --> 00:26:54,356
Yeah, but if we wait,
people could die.

599
00:26:54,380 --> 00:26:55,974
So, beyond an acute
cholinergic crisis,

600
00:26:55,998 --> 00:26:57,976
people could have serious
long-term disabilities...

601
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:00,667
I don't need to be educated on
the effects of organophosphates.

602
00:27:00,703 --> 00:27:03,820
Okay, Dr. Bell, we just
need to do the right thing.

603
00:27:13,698 --> 00:27:16,616
I can only see you
when I turn to look at you.

604
00:27:16,669 --> 00:27:18,930
When you stand to the right
of me, I can't see you at all.

605
00:27:18,954 --> 00:27:20,487
Must be because of the tumor.

606
00:27:20,523 --> 00:27:22,705
The bleeding is
causing some swelling,

607
00:27:22,741 --> 00:27:24,925
and that is what's
affecting your vision.

608
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:26,293
Well, will it get better?

609
00:27:26,328 --> 00:27:27,461
I-I can't go blind.

610
00:27:27,496 --> 00:27:28,689
We're giving you some steroids.

611
00:27:28,713 --> 00:27:30,125
We're gonna
decrease the swelling.

612
00:27:30,149 --> 00:27:32,766
Now, if we can get
that tumor out soon,

613
00:27:32,801 --> 00:27:34,012
- then you should regain
your vision.
- "If"?

614
00:27:34,036 --> 00:27:36,019
- Let's get it out now.
- Yes, I know.

615
00:27:36,055 --> 00:27:38,455
I am of the same mind.

616
00:27:38,491 --> 00:27:40,034
But your labile blood
pressure and heart rate

617
00:27:40,058 --> 00:27:41,836
haven't been responding
to the treatments.

618
00:27:41,860 --> 00:27:45,045
And I can't risk sending
you back into surgery

619
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:48,282
unless Dr. Hawkins
can come up with a plan

620
00:27:48,317 --> 00:27:51,835
to make sure that
you're safe in the OR.

621
00:27:51,870 --> 00:27:53,698
- What's the plan?
- Yes, Dr. Hawkins.

622
00:27:53,722 --> 00:27:56,106
What is the plan?

623
00:28:00,212 --> 00:28:03,497
John, I know you've been
scanned and examined up and down,

624
00:28:03,532 --> 00:28:07,917
but do you mind if I
take one more look?

625
00:28:21,766 --> 00:28:24,651
Did that start to hurt
after the accident?

626
00:28:24,686 --> 00:28:26,936
No, actually.

627
00:28:26,972 --> 00:28:30,440
That pain has been
on and off for a while.

628
00:28:30,475 --> 00:28:32,709
Sometimes it hurts
so bad, I feel like

629
00:28:32,744 --> 00:28:33,921
it's gonna rip right through me.

630
00:28:33,945 --> 00:28:36,113
Like today in the OR.

631
00:28:36,148 --> 00:28:37,381
And then...

632
00:28:37,416 --> 00:28:39,566
all of a sudden, it gets better.

633
00:28:40,619 --> 00:28:42,585
Now...

634
00:28:42,621 --> 00:28:44,788
I'm gonna untie your gown

635
00:28:44,823 --> 00:28:48,375
so I can get a good listen...

636
00:28:48,410 --> 00:28:51,127
to your lungs.

637
00:28:55,300 --> 00:28:57,267
What?

638
00:28:57,303 --> 00:28:58,930
What's wrong?

639
00:28:58,954 --> 00:29:01,922
There are blisters
on your shoulder.

640
00:29:01,957 --> 00:29:03,123
I did not see that earlier.

641
00:29:03,158 --> 00:29:04,953
Why the hell didn't
you see that earlier?

642
00:29:04,977 --> 00:29:07,072
That's your job. Didn't you
do a full physical examination?

643
00:29:07,096 --> 00:29:09,429
They-they weren't
there this morning.

644
00:29:09,464 --> 00:29:11,731
I'm sure. I would know.
I've had them in the past.

645
00:29:11,767 --> 00:29:14,151
That's why I hate the sun.

646
00:29:14,186 --> 00:29:17,237
And when we were outside, I
was covered from head to toe.

647
00:29:19,091 --> 00:29:20,323
Hyponatremia.

648
00:29:20,359 --> 00:29:22,042
Recurrent abdominal pain.

649
00:29:22,077 --> 00:29:23,326
Blistering skin lesions.

650
00:29:23,361 --> 00:29:25,145
Blistering.

651
00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:27,380
Blistering, blistering,
blistering skin lesions.

652
00:29:35,156 --> 00:29:37,090
I need a urine sample.

653
00:29:38,994 --> 00:29:39,994
Right now.

654
00:29:43,982 --> 00:29:46,149
<i>There's got to be a mistake.</i>

655
00:29:46,185 --> 00:29:47,134
I don't know.

656
00:29:47,169 --> 00:29:48,435
It doesn't make sense.

657
00:29:48,470 --> 00:29:50,164
We ship out hundreds
of thousands of units

658
00:29:50,188 --> 00:29:51,249
and only three people get sick?

659
00:29:51,273 --> 00:29:53,157
Well, it's not just three.

660
00:29:53,192 --> 00:29:55,959
No, I just found out
that two more patients

661
00:29:55,994 --> 00:29:58,006
have been diagnosed with
organophosphate poisoning

662
00:29:58,030 --> 00:29:59,857
- over at Atlanta General.
- Oh, my God.

663
00:29:59,881 --> 00:30:00,992
They're stable. They're
getting treatment,

664
00:30:01,016 --> 00:30:02,593
just like the ones
here at Chastain.

665
00:30:02,617 --> 00:30:03,783
Are they on 3B?

666
00:30:03,836 --> 00:30:04,785
They're on supplements.

667
00:30:04,820 --> 00:30:06,970
But if I ask for specifics,

668
00:30:07,005 --> 00:30:10,607
the doctors there will make
the same connection that we did.

669
00:30:10,643 --> 00:30:12,008
Then we test the facility,

670
00:30:12,043 --> 00:30:13,871
- we prove it's not us.
- Agreed, but...

671
00:30:15,514 --> 00:30:18,998
Zip is gonna start talking
about an exit strategy.

672
00:30:19,034 --> 00:30:21,351
- Wait, what? It's too soon.
- No, Andrea,

673
00:30:21,386 --> 00:30:24,955
there's a chance, no
matter what the percentage,

674
00:30:24,990 --> 00:30:28,408
that 3B is the culprit and
that we're dead in the water.

675
00:30:29,979 --> 00:30:32,829
I can't believe
this is happening.

676
00:30:32,864 --> 00:30:34,514
I-I...

677
00:30:34,549 --> 00:30:37,016
I have to call the partners.

678
00:30:43,992 --> 00:30:46,176
Your post-op CBC is stable.

679
00:30:46,211 --> 00:30:47,411
No more bleeding.

680
00:30:47,446 --> 00:30:48,556
Distal pulses are strong.

681
00:30:48,580 --> 00:30:51,014
Becky, can you wiggle your toes?

682
00:30:52,067 --> 00:30:53,067
Looks good.

683
00:30:54,069 --> 00:30:56,481
Recovering from major
surgery is challenging,

684
00:30:56,505 --> 00:30:58,366
so we will be
monitoring you closely.

685
00:30:58,390 --> 00:31:00,340
Thank you.

686
00:31:00,375 --> 00:31:02,308
And what about John?

687
00:31:02,344 --> 00:31:05,145
He didn't have surgery yet.

688
00:31:05,180 --> 00:31:06,229
Why?

689
00:31:06,265 --> 00:31:07,814
We don't know.

690
00:31:07,849 --> 00:31:10,234
But we do know his
doctors are working on it.

691
00:31:10,269 --> 00:31:11,901
What does that mean?

692
00:31:11,936 --> 00:31:14,070
Will he be okay?

693
00:31:15,090 --> 00:31:17,023
Can I be with him?

694
00:31:17,059 --> 00:31:18,191
First, you must get well.

695
00:31:18,227 --> 00:31:21,277
Then you can be strong for him.

696
00:31:21,313 --> 00:31:24,331
When he had brain
surgery eight years ago,

697
00:31:24,366 --> 00:31:27,345
I held his hand all night.

698
00:31:27,369 --> 00:31:31,337
Like I could keep him with
me, just by physically holding on.

699
00:31:31,372 --> 00:31:32,456
And it worked.

700
00:31:32,491 --> 00:31:34,540
Well, as soon as we can,

701
00:31:34,576 --> 00:31:36,576
we'll get you two
back together again.

702
00:31:41,099 --> 00:31:43,016
And now we have
urine in the sun.

703
00:31:43,052 --> 00:31:45,385
Dr. Hawkins, I'm starting
to lose my patience.

704
00:31:45,420 --> 00:31:47,070
Just wait.

705
00:31:47,105 --> 00:31:49,255
I am not gonna stand here

706
00:31:49,308 --> 00:31:51,602
and stare at another man's
urine with you while John's tumor

707
00:31:51,626 --> 00:31:53,410
continues to swell.

708
00:31:53,445 --> 00:31:55,679
We don't have time for this.

709
00:31:59,100 --> 00:32:01,518
It was time well spent.

710
00:32:04,956 --> 00:32:07,291
What-What's happening?

711
00:32:07,326 --> 00:32:09,760
John, this urine changed color.

712
00:32:09,795 --> 00:32:11,222
That explains what
happened in the OR

713
00:32:11,246 --> 00:32:14,163
and gives us a
diagnosis: porphyria.

714
00:32:14,199 --> 00:32:16,160
Porphyria's when you have an
excess of the chemical porphyrin

715
00:32:16,184 --> 00:32:18,000
and it builds up in your organs,

716
00:32:18,036 --> 00:32:20,604
and when that happens,
certain stressors, like...

717
00:32:20,639 --> 00:32:22,834
the intense lighting in
the OR, triggers a crisis

718
00:32:22,858 --> 00:32:27,460
that causes things like
blisters, stomach pain,

719
00:32:27,495 --> 00:32:28,929
and even organ damage.

720
00:32:28,964 --> 00:32:31,081
You got all that from my pee?

721
00:32:31,116 --> 00:32:34,079
Combined with your exam

722
00:32:34,103 --> 00:32:36,502
and history of previous
stomach pain and skin blisters.

723
00:32:36,538 --> 00:32:38,137
But yes,

724
00:32:38,190 --> 00:32:41,274
when the porphyrins turned
your urine dark in the sun,

725
00:32:41,310 --> 00:32:43,276
my clinical suspicion
was confirmed.

726
00:32:43,329 --> 00:32:45,529
So I've had this my whole life?

727
00:32:45,564 --> 00:32:48,614
Incredibly rare, easily missed,

728
00:32:48,650 --> 00:32:51,167
but the good news is...

729
00:32:52,220 --> 00:32:54,370
we can treat you.

730
00:32:56,875 --> 00:32:59,041
We'll be sending
confirmatory labs of course,

731
00:32:59,077 --> 00:33:01,961
but I am confident you
will be back in the OR soon.

732
00:33:02,014 --> 00:33:04,497
Which Dr. Cain and I
will be prepping for you.

733
00:33:04,532 --> 00:33:06,933
<i>I made a list</i>

734
00:33:06,968 --> 00:33:09,063
of all the meds that can be
fatal to a porphyria patient.

735
00:33:09,087 --> 00:33:10,949
Avoid these at all costs.

736
00:33:10,973 --> 00:33:12,951
I haven't had a porphyria
patient since residency.

737
00:33:12,975 --> 00:33:15,659
Yep, this is a unique
case. That's exactly why

738
00:33:15,694 --> 00:33:17,288
I made a list for everyone.

739
00:33:17,312 --> 00:33:19,479
Propofol for
anesthesia, that's safe.

740
00:33:19,514 --> 00:33:21,409
Morphine's okay. Just let
me know before you give

741
00:33:21,433 --> 00:33:23,060
- any antibiotics.
- Dr. Hawkins is right.

742
00:33:23,084 --> 00:33:25,134
We all need to
review the drug list.

743
00:33:25,170 --> 00:33:27,698
And the reason John
crashed in the OR before

744
00:33:27,722 --> 00:33:29,917
was because of these intense
lights, so we got these filters.

745
00:33:29,941 --> 00:33:32,403
We'll still be able to see, but
they change the wavelength

746
00:33:32,427 --> 00:33:34,189
of the light that
hits John's body.

747
00:33:34,213 --> 00:33:36,173
Avoiding a porphyric crisis.

748
00:33:44,923 --> 00:33:47,507
What the hell happened?

749
00:33:47,542 --> 00:33:48,819
She came out fine
after the surgery,

750
00:33:48,843 --> 00:33:50,938
then she went into V
tach and lost her pressure.

751
00:33:50,962 --> 00:33:53,980
Hold compressions.
Checking a rhythm.

752
00:33:54,015 --> 00:33:56,433
Damn, she's still in V fib.
We need to shock again.

753
00:33:56,468 --> 00:33:57,851
Charging to 200.

754
00:33:57,886 --> 00:33:58,886
Clear.

755
00:33:58,921 --> 00:34:00,665
Restart compressions.

756
00:34:00,689 --> 00:34:02,272
I'll take over.

757
00:34:02,307 --> 00:34:03,273
Code labs are back.

758
00:34:03,308 --> 00:34:05,442
Hemoglobin is stable.

759
00:34:05,477 --> 00:34:06,537
She's not losing blood.

760
00:34:06,561 --> 00:34:07,994
But her calcium is under five.

761
00:34:08,030 --> 00:34:09,373
That's not doing
her heart any favors.

762
00:34:09,397 --> 00:34:11,081
Okay, we need more calcium.

763
00:34:11,116 --> 00:34:12,744
One gram of
calcium chloride, now.

764
00:34:12,768 --> 00:34:14,729
We ordered it hours ago. There's
a calcium chloride shortage.

765
00:34:14,753 --> 00:34:16,586
Take it from the crash cart.

766
00:34:16,621 --> 00:34:17,966
She should have
received more calcium

767
00:34:17,990 --> 00:34:19,372
with her blood transfusions.

768
00:34:19,407 --> 00:34:21,069
This is what happens
when drug companies

769
00:34:21,093 --> 00:34:25,078
discontinue products that
